# Session log (SESSION_LOG.md)

The maintainer works on **Mac and Windows**; **Cursor chat history does not sync** between machines. They rely on **`SESSION_LOG.md`** (committed with the repo) as the **shared notebook** so the other machine always knows what happened, what was decided, and what to do next.

## When to update

**On every user message you respond to in this repo:** before you finish the turn, **append** to **`SESSION_LOG.md`** (new dated stub or add bullets under today’s heading).

- **Code / config / content changed:** same batch as the diff; include files touched and operational notes.
- **No repo changes (question-only, diagnosis, “run this”):** still append a **short handoff** (what was asked, answer/decision, any commands run, blockers). One tight paragraph is enough.

Also keep the existing habit: any **meaningful** change batch should include an updated log **before** commit or push.

## What to include

- **Date** (and short session title if helpful). Optional: **machine** if the user said (e.g. Windows 11).
- **Summary bullets** of what changed or what was discussed.
- **Files touched** (added / updated) when useful for handoff.
- **Operational notes** (env vars, restart steps, deploy caveats) when relevant.
- **Next steps** for the other machine when non-obvious.

## Out of scope

- Never commit **`.env.local`**—session log may mention env **names** only.
